The paper proposes a method for improving the performance of deep neural network models in human pose estimation through adversarial data augmentation. This involves jointly optimizing data augmentation and network training by designing an augmentation network that competes against a target network. This approach is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and graphics (cs.GR).
